{"TopicId":219323,"ForumId":144,"TopicTitle":"SAS does not hold orientation during timewarp","CreatedByName":"Vl3d","CreatedById":219348,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-09-06T07:57:44Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Vl3d","CreatedById":219348,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-09-06T07:57:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EReported Version:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0v0.1.4 (latest) |\u00A0\u003Cstrong\u003EMods:\u00A0\u003C/strong\u003Enone | \u003Cstrong\u003ECan replicate without mods?\u003C/strong\u003E Yes\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EOS:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0Windows 11 | \u003Cstrong\u003ECPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0AMD Ryzen 5 7600x | \u003Cstrong\u003EGPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0Nvidia RTX 4070 | \u003Cstrong\u003ERAM\u003Cspan\u003E:\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E32 GB DDR5\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI know this was expected behavior in KSP 1 and we needed a mod to fix it (ex. Persistent Rotation), but how can we use acceleration during time warp if \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E does not maintain heading?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIMO if \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E is on, the craft should hold the set orientation / direction / heading during time warp. I consider \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E being automatically disabled during time warp a bug.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-09-06T11:49:09Z\u0022 title=\u002209/06/2023 11:49  AM\u0022 data-short=\u0022Sep 6\u0022\u003ESeptember 6, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by Anth12\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Sun_Serega","CreatedById":232049,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-01-06T19:34:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMade a bug-fixing mod because couldn\u0027t wait for a proper implementation:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u0022232049\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed1502435540\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/topic/222674-sased-warp/?do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:194px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat said, please don\u0027t consider it a solution. It\u0027s only good enough as a hotfix.\u003Cbr\u003E\nAnd it doesn\u0027t exist for this particular bug-report, it\u0027s more of a general improvements for \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E and thrust during warp.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vortygont","CreatedById":223549,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-09-08T10:22:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nVery important topic. We have acceleration during timewarp and integrable trajectories but this function is\u00A0underutilized. So with new possibilities it\u0027s still impossible to fly ion tug or another vessel with low thrust from low orbits of big planets, because you can\u0027t\u00A0 maintain orientation during time warp to have spiral escape trajectory. I feel this feauter can be implemented in current timewarp acceleration function relatively easy\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Anth","CreatedById":161238,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-09-08T21:30:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n7 upvotes? Nice.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI mean... 8\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vortygont","CreatedById":223549,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-09-09T10:14:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224320632\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022219323\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221694208634\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022161238\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Anth12\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n12 hours ago, Anth12 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n7 upvotes? Nice.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI mean... 8\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA whole 24 upvotes\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:cool:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cool.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:cool:\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"cocoscacao","CreatedById":225696,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-09-09T10:34:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI am surprised... no, SHOCKED, in all caps, for dramatic effect, with an explanation that all caps was used for dramatic effect, that this issue hasn\u0027t been reported earlier.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Anth","CreatedById":161238,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-09-09T11:36:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224320821\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022219323\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221694254448\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022223549\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Vortygont\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Vortygont said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA whole 24 upvotes\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:cool:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cool.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:cool:\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\nThat was fast.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"HieroGriff","CreatedById":232015,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-01-07T13:07:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI haven\u0027t progressed far enough in the game yet for this bug to be an issue for me but when i saw your mod show up on \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003ECKAN\u003C/abbr\u003E i came to take a look, so thanks in advance!\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Temporal Wolf","CreatedById":117332,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-01-12T00:45:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis seems like less a \u0022does not hold orientation\u0022 and more a \u0022craft can\u0027t rotate during time warp\u0022, which definitely seems like a double edged sword:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E works during time warp/craft can rotate, then heading instability becomes an issue while burning under time warp... which is not a good thing in my book.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}